column3:
On a scale of 1 to 5, please rate your overall opinion of the Black Tie Tailgate.

-
column4: What did you like best about the Black Tie Tailgate? - Open-Ended Response
that the money made goes to CHOP
Less crowded view of the show
Atmosphere, flow of people around the event.
I love seeing all of the new cars. The jeep presentation is always fun!
The chance to educate ourselves on new products and visit with our clients
Lively upbeat atmosphere, an enjoyable evening
Seeing all of the cars up close and being able to compare them to one another
Seeing all the cars in a relaxed atmosphere and knowing that the proceeds went to charity
Being able to explore the cars and not have to worry about lines/ too many people surrounding

Totally impressed with the affair!! Something for everyone!! A full night of fun, food, education, loved the antique car display, Pope Mobile, simulated race track, Jeep ride exhibition, friendliness and helpfulness of the staff, etc.
Food & less crowded than the show
the atmosphere and the ease of using public transportation
the opportunity to actually sit in the vehicles.
The presentation on the red carpet
Exciting evening that benefitted an extremely worthy cause and a chance to have a night out with just my wife and myself sans kids
The attendee,s very friendly. Everyone was polite but ready to party. Terrific event.
Festive atmosphere for a great cause
The glamour and sparkle and beauty.
Seeing the cars without major crowds
I love cars and the venue coupled with food and drinks linked to Children's Hospital make it a must do.
All of the Cars on display and JellyRoll performing at the end.
open bar, not crowded to see the cars
I liked being able to dress up with my wife and the cause was important to us.
Was well planned out- plenty of spaces for food and drink
That it was for a good cause and I got to get dressed up

food, atmosphere, fun night with friends, selfie sticks

that it was a private showing
No children. No mass of people so very easy to see cars
